review_blob:
Not sure what all the hoopla is about this IPA. Yea it's good, but I don't know why people travel far and wide for it and buy out all of Whole Foods stock as soon as it comes in. 
Anyway, good beer- too much hype. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Only Sierra could have tamed this hoppy beast of a beer. Well balanced with citrus and the hops are not overwhelming. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

I was totally blown away by this mellow flavorful double stout. Since it's a Green Flash beer I expected to be knocked on my ass by An intense beer, but I'm floored by all the subtle nuances this brew offers.  

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

I really love this Imperial Red. It's big and hoppy with a lot of complexity. Don't confuse this with an IPA, this hoppy monster finishes smooth. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Love this beer. Comes in a can so not much head when pours in a glass. Nice lingering hoppy finish dry hopped to perfection. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Very misleading.  Great label and deScription, but when it comes down to drink ability this Imperial Stout falls short.

beer_name: Black Diamond Peak XV Imperial Porter

review_blob:
Very smooth IPA like it says on the bottle. A little too fizzy for me. Taste like  the other line of beers from Widmer. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

On a cold dark night this beer is just what the doctor ordered. One of the more flavorful winter Warmers.

A very mild IPA. Very little hops and kind of sweet.  I much prefer Drakes 1500 Pale Ale. It has more hops and drinks like an IPA.
